comment: Sentence 1 = physical face, sentence 2 = confronted with people face-to-face
S1 refers to the front of something while S2 more refers to being in the presence of something i.e. standing in front of something, so highly related
S1 face means the representative symbol/mascot of something while S2 refers to a human's face which is what S1 is derived from
Since S2 can't be replaced with “front”, I don't see them as closely related
S1 is more appearance rather than front/presence but is still related to S2
I don’t know what a “face of horrible decline” means.
